9
00:00:23,220 --> 00:00:26,100
♫Where’s that love people are saying?♫

10
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:29,500
♫To always be by each other’s sides♫

11
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:32,580
♫The love that’s willing to sacrifice everything♫

12
00:00:32,580 --> 00:00:35,580
♫Everything even my own life♫

13
00:00:35,580 --> 00:00:39,060
♫Do they really exist? I’d rather not believe it♫

14
00:00:39,060 --> 00:00:42,140
♫I don’t think I’ll ever fall for anyone♫

15
00:00:42,140 --> 00:00:45,380
♫Love? I don’t find it interesting♫

16
00:00:45,380 --> 00:00:48,460
♫Sorry about that♫

17
00:00:48,940 --> 00:00:51,500
♫But then who are you?♫

18
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:55,500
♫To make my heart keep fluttering♫

19
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:57,900
♫Please tell me♫

20
00:00:58,140 --> 00:01:01,220
♫What’s happening with my heart?♫

21
00:01:01,220 --> 00:01:04,580
♫It can’t be, why am I feeling this?♫

22
00:01:04,580 --> 00:01:07,660
♫Oh, my heart is pounding so fast♫

23
00:01:07,660 --> 00:01:10,740
♫Time freezes whenever I see you♫

24
00:01:10,740 --> 00:01:14,100
♫I wonder why every time you smile♫

25
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:17,380
♫Something in your eyes make me go weak♫

26
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:20,580
♫Oh no, this is real–it’s not a dream♫

27
00:01:20,580 --> 00:01:23,460
♫Or is the love that people are saying...♫

28
00:01:23,460 --> 00:01:25,340
♫Is it you?♫

29
00:01:30,220 --> 00:01:32,060
♫Is it you?♫

30
00:01:32,060 --> 00:01:35,620
[Flaming Chains of Love]

31
00:01:36,259 --> 00:01:38,220
[Surat Thani]

32
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:50,100
[Akanee Crushing Plant]

33
00:01:58,820 --> 00:02:00,820
[Akanee Oil Palm Plantation]

34
00:02:07,660 --> 00:02:09,259
[Akanee Fisherman’s Wharf]

35
00:02:22,760 --> 00:02:26,460
Ladies and gentlemen, it’s time for the honorary award–

36
00:02:26,780 --> 00:02:30,900
Rattana Narai Award for the year 2026.

37
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:37,579
It’s an award given to those who have tremendously contributed to the benefits and well-being of Surat Thani.

38
00:02:37,579 --> 00:02:45,340
And for this year, our committee has unanimously agreed that this award shall go to…

39
00:02:45,340 --> 00:02:49,180
Mr. Akanee Watinwanich from the Akanee Empire.

40
00:02:55,180 --> 00:02:56,260
Thank you.

41
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:37,540
On this occasion, would you please kindly say a few words to all of our guests?

42
00:03:43,060 --> 00:03:44,140
Thank you.

43
00:03:44,780 --> 00:03:51,140
I believe many of you here might only see how successful I am now.

44
00:03:52,329 --> 00:03:55,460
How the Akanee Empire has expanded extensively.

45
00:03:56,579 --> 00:04:00,820
But for me and the Akanee Empire to be where we are today,

46
00:04:01,580 --> 00:04:05,740
I’m telling you–it’s not easy at all.

47
00:04:06,620 --> 00:04:14,940
Every step I took was filled with obstacles…and those who wished to get rid of me.

48
00:04:20,959 --> 00:04:26,100
I’m not afraid! I’ve won this auction for the mining concession fairly and legally.

49
00:04:26,620 --> 00:04:28,620
I don’t care if anyone doesn’t want to play by the rules.

50
00:04:29,820 --> 00:04:30,780
Let’s go.

51
00:04:31,330 --> 00:04:32,300
Master, look out!

52
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:33,380
[Gunshot]

53
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:35,000
This way! Quick!

54
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:46,300
Believe it or not, I used to get assassinated just because I got in the way of some powerful people.

55
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:49,060
I almost couldn’t make it out alive.

56
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:58,220
But I still stand firm in my morals, and never will I bow down to any misconduct.

57
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:05,060
And that is why our Akanee Empire

58
00:05:06,420 --> 00:05:11,020
is able to stand firm and become formidable today. Thank you.

59
00:05:11,020 --> 00:05:13,580
[Applause]

60
00:05:25,060 --> 00:05:27,180
[Guest]: Mr. Akanee, this way please. Can I take a picture with you?

61
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:31,380
Thank you.

62
00:05:36,580 --> 00:05:38,780
[Guest]: Thank you.
[Akanee]: Thank you. My pleasure.

63
00:05:41,659 --> 00:05:42,860
Thank you.

64
00:05:45,380 --> 00:05:47,300
[Guest]: Congratulations.
[Akanee]: Thank you.

65
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:49,500
Thank you very much.

66
00:05:53,020 --> 00:05:53,860
Yod.

67
00:05:55,260 --> 00:05:56,060
Yes, Boss?

68
00:05:58,200 --> 00:05:59,900
Has Roong arrived in Surat yet?

69
00:06:00,060 --> 00:06:04,540
Yes, I already sent someone to pick her up and take her to the main house.

70
00:06:04,660 --> 00:06:11,740
Good. I’ll move my little one to live in the main house so that she can help look after my business.

71
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:17,260
Whoa! Will Young Master agree though? Even Miss Wanna doesn’t get to stay there.

72
00:06:17,260 --> 00:06:21,620
It’s not for her to decide. Fai has never slept at the main house anyway.

73
00:06:21,940 --> 00:06:25,820
Also, she hardly helps me look after the business.

74
00:06:25,820 --> 00:06:27,860
Only God knows why she keeps avoiding me.

75
00:06:27,930 --> 00:06:28,980
Just for the time being[whispering].

76
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:33,220
Fine, answer me–have you seen her today?

77
00:06:33,659 --> 00:06:37,580
Do you know where your Young Master is right now?

78
00:06:39,060 --> 00:06:41,700
Smile, huh?

79
00:06:53,940 --> 00:06:55,300
[Watinwanich No. 4]

80
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:56,900
[Young Master]

81
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:22,860
Here, the Master’s woman you’ve asked me to look into.

82
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,980
Is Dad seeing a girl his daughter's age?

83
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:42,659
He has rented a flat for this girl and even paid for her education until she finished college.

84
00:08:42,659 --> 00:08:46,860
People in the neighbourhood say he comes to visit her every week.

85
00:08:47,620 --> 00:08:51,740
[Phone ringing]

86
00:08:54,460 --> 00:08:55,330
Yes, Paen?

87
00:08:55,960 --> 00:09:02,980
Young Master! The Master just brought his girl into the main house. She is moving in.

88
00:09:05,730 --> 00:09:06,530
What?

89
00:09:18,780 --> 00:09:22,940
[Paen]: Finally, Miss! You’re just in time.

90
00:09:22,940 --> 00:09:26,380
I’m about to take her bags upstairs.

91
00:09:26,380 --> 00:09:30,100
[Paen]: Over there, Miss. Look!

92
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:33,820
Paen, throw them away!

93
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,260
Yes, Miss!

94
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,100
What are you doing?

95
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,980
Throwing away trash, obviously.

96
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:46,220
Bring my little one’s bags upstairs, right now!

97
00:09:46,220 --> 00:09:48,100
- Yes, Master.
-Throw them away!

98
00:09:48,100 --> 00:09:49,260
Okay, Miss.

99
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:50,460
I said take them upstairs!

100
00:09:50,460 --> 00:09:52,140
[Paen]: Yes!
- [Akanee]: NOW!

101
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:56,500
Yes.

102
00:09:57,930 --> 00:09:59,140
I’m going.

103
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:02,700
You have no shame calling her your little one.

104
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:05,900
I already told you not to bring any of your women into this house.

105
00:10:06,460 --> 00:10:08,660
I don’t care how many girls you’re seeing.

106
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:11,260
But this house isn’t a place for your chicks.

107
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:16,100
Seriously, can’t you just calm down a bit?

108
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,420
Then why didn’t you keep your words?

109
00:10:18,420 --> 00:10:22,060
This is Mum’s house. You have no right to bring your new lover here!

110
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:26,020
I never said I’ll bring my new lover here.

111
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:30,940
If she’s not your new lover, then who the heck is she? Where is she?

112
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:33,860
There she is.

113
00:10:54,560 --> 00:10:56,220
Do you remember her?

114
00:10:58,700 --> 00:10:59,940
No.

115
00:11:01,530 --> 00:11:03,300
That’s Kaphrao.

116
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:11,340
The bloody Guinea Pig!

117
00:11:13,330 --> 00:11:14,780
Do you remember me now?

118
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:21,380
[We all have someone we remember from our childhood.]

119
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:25,780
[Kaphrao and I are like that. E

120
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:27,860
[the annoying rascal pest called Kaphrao.]

121
00:11:29,130 --> 00:11:33,900
[I also will never forget Buffalo Fai who always picked on me]

122
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:37,700
[and did a number on me. Ten years isn’t too late for revenge.]

123
00:11:55,530 --> 00:11:56,860
This is Kaphrao.

124
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:03,540
She’ll live with us here. Think of her as your little sister.

125
00:12:07,530 --> 00:12:09,180
Kaphrao, this is Fai.

126
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:43,300
Look after her and play with her, okay?

127
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:48,700
Kaphrao, always listen to your sister.

128
00:12:54,730 --> 00:12:59,220
Dad said she’s the daughter of a worker who just passed away.

129
00:12:59,580 --> 00:13:04,700
She doesn’t have any parents now so he has to take her in.

130
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:07,660
But to adopt her as his own daughter?

131
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:11,660
What if she’s actually his mistress’ kid?

132
00:13:15,460 --> 00:13:17,340
Listen to me, Fai.

133
00:13:19,130 --> 00:13:21,340
You should stay away from her.

134
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:24,980
She’ll take everything from you.

135
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:26,380
Do you understand?

136
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:42,900
Fai…

137
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:44,740
When will you stop following me?

138
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:46,900
But I want to play with you.

139
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:49,220
But I don’t want to play with you.

140
00:13:49,930 --> 00:13:57,340
Wait for me, Fai. Big Sis, please wait. Fai!

141
00:13:57,340 --> 00:13:59,620
Go away! I don’t have a younger sister!

142
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:03,940
Fai. Fai. Fai.

143
00:14:03,940 --> 00:14:05,500
Geez, I said leave me alone!

144
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:09,380
[Kaphrao]: Fai. Fai.
[Fai]: Leave me alone!

145
00:14:10,860 --> 00:14:14,700
[Kaphrao]: Fai, it hurts!
[Akanee]: Kaphrao!

146
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:15,500
Serve you right!

147
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:19,660
- It hurts. It hurts.
- Are you okay, sweetie?

148
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:22,100
[Akanee]: Where does it hurt?
[Kaphrao]: Here.

149
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:26,300
Fai, why do you always pick on her?

150
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:29,580
If I see you do it again, I’ll give you a smack!

151
00:14:29,860 --> 00:14:33,660
But I don’t have a younger sister. I don’t like the Guinea Pig!

152
00:14:34,060 --> 00:14:36,340
Fai! Fai!

153
00:14:38,900 --> 00:14:39,960
Does it hurt here?

154
00:14:42,260 --> 00:14:44,460
Please don’t be mad at her, okay?

155
00:14:44,460 --> 00:14:46,700
[Akanee]: I’ll fix the wound for you.
- [That annoying brat.]

156
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:53,380
[She only came here to steal Dad’s love from me.]
[Akanee]: There, there! All good now, right?

157
00:14:53,380 --> 00:14:56,780
Come, let’s go inside.

158
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:58,140
Bring your toys too.

159
00:15:00,730 --> 00:15:03,860
This one is for Fai. And this one is for Uncle.

160
00:15:04,660 --> 00:15:09,180
Thank you, my dear. Let me have a bite.

161
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:16,580
It’s terrible.

162
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:20,000
Don’t listen to her.

163
00:15:20,660 --> 00:15:21,730
Let me try it.

164
00:15:28,860 --> 00:15:34,020
Wow, it’s so good! Well done! Give me a peck.

165
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:36,620
[In his eyes, whatever she did pleased him.]

166
00:15:36,620 --> 00:15:39,220
[Akanee]: Can you feed your uncle too?
[But whatever I did was wrong.]

167
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,740
Let me play it too.

168
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:53,980
I don’t want to.

169
00:15:54,730 --> 00:15:56,140
But I want to play it.

170
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:58,460
It’s mine. I’m not giving it to you.

171
00:15:58,930 --> 00:16:00,140
Fai!

172
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:02,940
Serve you right! You should’ve given me when I asked you nicely.

173
00:16:03,130 --> 00:16:04,900
Why did you break it then?

174
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:06,980
You didn’t give it to me when I asked you nicely.

175
00:16:07,330 --> 00:16:08,900
But it’s mine!

176
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:11,420
Fine, you want it this way, huh?

177
00:16:16,930 --> 00:16:18,180
It’s mine!

178
00:16:18,180 --> 00:16:21,300
[We always fought like cat and dog, until one day…]

179
00:16:21,530 --> 00:16:22,580
I’m not giving it to you!

180
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:24,780
But I want to play it!

181
00:16:24,860 --> 00:16:26,200
I’m not letting you play it!

182
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:27,260
But I want to!

183
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:28,860
No, you can’t!

184
00:16:29,460 --> 00:16:30,900
Then you can’t play it too!

185
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:44,140
Should we play together?

186
00:16:44,860 --> 00:16:47,700
Do you want to play with me now?

187
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:50,000
Yes, but you have to listen to me.

188
00:16:51,930 --> 00:16:54,100
Okay, follow me then.

189
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:03,460
[Worker]: Mee! Mee! Got packages from the wharf!

190
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:09,420
Come here, quick!

191
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:14,819
Let’s play hide and seek. But you have to be the seeker first, okay?

192
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:17,380
[Kaphrao]: But…
[Fai]: You can quit if you don’t want to.

193
00:17:18,930 --> 00:17:20,420
I’ll do it.

194
00:17:21,460 --> 00:17:22,530
Then, get in there.

195
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:27,099
It’s dark. I’m scared.

196
00:17:27,859 --> 00:17:30,960
You said you’d listen to me. If you chicken out, then let’s not play together.

197
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,660
I’ll do it.

198
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:36,980
Get in there then.

199
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:53,500
I’m scared.

200
00:17:53,560 --> 00:17:54,940
Are you going to do it or not?

201
00:17:57,460 --> 00:18:00,660
Turn around and close your eyes, then count to twenty.

202
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:10,140
1, 2, 3…

203
00:18:10,700 --> 00:18:11,660
Slowly.

204
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:25,140
4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11…

205
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:41,020
How could she disappear? There were so many people there?

206
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:47,500
Fai! Where were you playing with your sister earlier?

207
00:18:48,130 --> 00:18:50,780
I played hide and seek with her on the truck.

208
00:18:51,160 --> 00:18:54,700
But when I went back, the truck was gone.

209
00:18:56,700 --> 00:19:00,460
Probably the fish truck. But we don’t know which one.

210
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:05,540
It must have gone far now. Damn it!

211
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,940
Kaphrao! Kaphrao!

212
00:19:17,940 --> 00:19:19,540
[Worker]: I’m sorry, Master. I didn’t mean it.

213
00:19:19,540 --> 00:19:20,820
[Worker]: I’m sorry.

214
00:19:20,820 --> 00:19:22,140
[Worker]: I’m sorry.
[Akanee] Kaphrao!

215
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:25,820
She’s ice-cold. Why is her body so cold?

216
00:19:25,820 --> 00:19:27,820
Kaphrao. Let’s go!

217
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:29,540
Will she die?

218
00:19:29,540 --> 00:19:30,500
[Akanee]: Yod, open the door!

219
00:19:30,530 --> 00:19:31,330
[Yod]: Yes, Boss!

220
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:34,300
Stay with me, Kaphrao. Quick!

221
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:35,400
Let’s go!

222
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:36,960
[Akanee]: Hurry up, Yod!

223
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:38,060
[Yod]: Young Master!

224
00:19:39,060 --> 00:19:40,220
[Akanee]: Hang in there, Kaphrao.

225
00:19:40,930 --> 00:19:42,380
- Let’s go, Yod!
Yes, sir!

226
00:19:49,330 --> 00:19:53,420
Luckily, we found her quite fast. Otherwise, she might have been dead.

227
00:19:53,530 --> 00:19:54,740
Do you know that?

228
00:19:55,300 --> 00:20:00,420
You really went too far this time. I have to punish you.

229
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:02,980
Dad, I didn’t mean it.

230
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:08,700
Turn around now.

231
00:20:09,360 --> 00:20:10,780
I said turn around!

232
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:15,940
Remember, don’t ever do that again.

233
00:20:20,060 --> 00:20:22,620
- Dad! It hurts!
- [Akanee]: Don’t you dare do that again!

234
00:20:22,620 --> 00:20:23,980
[Fai]: It hurts!
[Akanee]: Don’t do it again!

235
00:20:23,980 --> 00:20:25,100
[Panee]: Stop it!
[Akanee]: Don’t ever do that again.

236
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:26,460
[Fai]: It hurts!
[Akanee]: Stop bullying your sister!

237
00:20:26,500 --> 00:20:27,300
That’s enough! She’s just a child.

238
00:20:29,930 --> 00:20:34,100
You’ve always spoiled her rotten, that’s why she’s like this!

239
00:20:35,060 --> 00:20:37,220
I didn’t mean it.

240
00:20:37,260 --> 00:20:40,460
You didn’t? How many times was it already?

241
00:20:40,930 --> 00:20:42,860
She doesn’t like Kaphrao.

242
00:20:43,500 --> 00:20:44,560
They don’t like each other.

243
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:47,460
This is all because you force them to live under one roof.

244
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:56,540
Fine! If you hate her that much, I’ll raise her somewhere else.

245
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:59,260
You will never see her again!

246
00:21:09,530 --> 00:21:19,420
My dear. Does it hurt? My sweetheart.

247
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:29,180
There, there. It’s all right now.

248
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:41,740
[Kaphrao]: Long time no see, Buffalo Fai.

249
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:48,420
That side piece he’s been keeping and even paid for her college is you?

250
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:54,980
Yes, Kaphrao already graduated.

251
00:21:54,980 --> 00:21:58,020
So, I want her to stay here to help with my work.

252
00:21:59,900 --> 00:22:02,420
Are you saying this Gremlin will take my job?

253
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:04,420
But you hate coming into the office.

254
00:22:04,420 --> 00:22:06,940
And you never come to the meeting.

255
00:22:06,940 --> 00:22:09,780
So, I have to find someone who’s willing to work.

256
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:11,540
But I’m not okay with her!

257
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:14,900
I can’t help you with that.

258
00:22:15,380 --> 00:22:20,820
I know you don’t want to work with me.

259
00:22:20,820 --> 00:22:22,460
You’ve been avoiding me.

260
00:22:22,460 --> 00:22:27,980
From now on, if you have anything to talk to me–just tell Kaphrao.

261
00:22:27,980 --> 00:22:31,500
And if there’s anything I want to talk to you about, I’ll also let Kapharo know.

262
00:22:31,860 --> 00:22:32,660
Okay?

263
00:22:32,930 --> 00:22:34,540
No, not okay!

264
00:22:34,540 --> 00:22:36,340
It doesn’t matter.

265
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:38,530
I’m not asking for your approval anyway.

266
00:22:39,460 --> 00:22:40,460
Fine!

267
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:43,530
I’ll let this Gremlin work here.

268
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:47,340
But she can’t stay in this house no matter what.

269
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:50,420
And don’t you dare call me Sister.

270
00:22:50,560 --> 00:22:52,260
I’m not your sibling!

271
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:10,100
Please don’t mind her.

272
00:23:11,760 --> 00:23:17,820
Her mother passed away when she was little. I buried myself in work after that and hardly had time for her.

273
00:23:17,820 --> 00:23:20,900
And all Aunt Panee did was pamper her.

274
00:23:22,900 --> 00:23:23,900
I understand.

275
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:29,660
About the place to stay, I can go live at the worker’s cabin.

276
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:32,330
I don’t want Fai to hate me even more.

277
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:41,140
No, don’t do that. I want you to stay here as my own niece–not my employee.

278
00:23:41,660 --> 00:23:46,660
Please. I want to start from there so that I could learn about work along the way,

279
00:23:46,660 --> 00:23:49,500
and make friends with the workers too.

280
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:53,420
It’ll be easier for me when I have to deal with them in the future.

281
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:58,660
Okay, if that’s what you want. I don’t want to force you.

282
00:23:59,260 --> 00:24:00,260
Thank you, Uncle.

283
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:06,780
Then, after we finish eating, I’ll ask Yod to drop you off at the cabin.

284
00:24:06,780 --> 00:24:11,220
And tomorrow, I’ll give you a tour around the empire myself.

285
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:14,500
Sounds great. I’ll be waiting early in the morning.

286
00:24:14,530 --> 00:24:15,700
I’ll pick you up tomorrow.

287
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:16,980
Let’s eat.

288
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:17,800
Yes.

289
00:24:17,860 --> 00:24:22,940
Here, the crispy omelette. It’s a must-try.

290
00:24:23,330 --> 00:24:25,340
- Thank you.
- You’re welcome.

291
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:29,940
Is it good?

292
00:24:31,620 --> 00:24:37,620
Oh, this one is the best. It’s really hard to come by.

293
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:47,060
I never thought Ak would bring this girl back into the house again.

294
00:24:48,860 --> 00:24:50,260
I completely forgot about her.

295
00:24:50,260 --> 00:24:52,540
I didn’t even recognise her when we met at first.

296
00:24:52,700 --> 00:24:57,100
But will you be okay if that girl will be working here?

297
00:24:57,260 --> 00:25:00,530
Absolutely not. But I can't say anything much to Dad now.

298
00:25:03,100 --> 00:25:09,180
Ak might see her as a niece but it doesn’t change the fact that that girl isn’t his biological kid.

299
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:12,100
Besides, she’s all grown up now.

300
00:25:12,130 --> 00:25:15,260
What if she tries to seduce him for his money?

301
00:25:16,500 --> 00:25:19,740
I don’t think so. Dad probably isn’t into someone that young.

302
00:25:20,800 --> 00:25:23,580
It’s better to be safe than sorry.

303
00:25:23,580 --> 00:25:27,540
You must keep an eye on her. Understood?

304
00:25:27,980 --> 00:25:31,860
Be careful, or else she might soon become your stepmother.

305
00:25:36,340 --> 00:25:40,500
If that’s the case, then she’ll have to go over my dead body first.

306
00:25:56,760 --> 00:25:57,980
It’s this one.

307
00:25:59,900 --> 00:26:04,100
Thank you so much, Uncle Yod. I can take it from here.

308
00:26:05,900 --> 00:26:09,340
Are you sure you’re going to stay here?

309
00:26:11,460 --> 00:26:14,100
Yes, I’d get to make more friends too.

310
00:26:15,530 --> 00:26:17,820
Up to you then.

311
00:26:18,100 --> 00:26:20,300
I’ll bring you a bicycle tomorrow.

312
00:26:20,300 --> 00:26:24,820
The office is quite far. You’d better ride a bike there.

313
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:26,460
Thank you.

314
00:26:26,760 --> 00:26:30,930
I’m off then. Call me if you need anything. My house is next door.

315
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:34,260
Oh, about the key–I already put it in the lock over there.

316
00:26:36,560 --> 00:26:38,540
Thank you again, Uncle Yod.

317
00:26:38,730 --> 00:26:41,180
Sure you can handle it?

318
00:26:42,760 --> 00:26:43,780
Yes.

319
00:26:44,860 --> 00:26:45,660
See you then.

320
00:26:45,660 --> 00:26:46,540
Bye.

321
00:28:01,360 --> 00:28:02,740
Who is it?

322
00:28:10,660 --> 00:28:11,860
Hi there!

323
00:28:13,700 --> 00:28:14,500
Hello.

324
00:28:16,260 --> 00:28:19,660
I’m Bua. Young Master has sent me to stay here with you.

325
00:28:20,100 --> 00:28:20,930
Stay here with me?

326
00:28:21,260 --> 00:28:25,560
Yes. She said you’re a girl and came here alone so she’s worried.

327
00:28:27,730 --> 00:28:30,260
More like to spy on me.

328
00:28:33,060 --> 00:28:35,530
Well then, I’m going in.

329
00:28:44,060 --> 00:28:46,340
It’s even bigger than my house on the island.

330
00:28:51,460 --> 00:28:57,460
Hey, it’s all right. Relax–feel free to be yourself.

331
00:28:57,500 --> 00:28:58,300
Okay.

332
00:29:00,100 --> 00:29:01,330
Do you work here, Bua?

333
00:29:02,730 --> 00:29:07,820
Yes, my house is on Young Master’s private island. My dad is a fisherman.

334
00:29:07,860 --> 00:29:15,300
But since I want to have a boyfriend, and there aren’t so many people on the island; I figured it’s better to be here.

335
00:29:17,060 --> 00:29:17,860
I see.

336
00:29:28,260 --> 00:29:33,180
Listen, Miss, if you want to know anything, you can always ask me.

337
00:29:33,180 --> 00:29:36,820
I might come from the island but I know everything about everyone here.

338
00:29:36,820 --> 00:29:39,820
Oh, and I’ll take this room then. It’s still empty, isn’t it?

339
00:29:39,820 --> 00:29:43,780
By the way, I’ll go shower first–feeling all sweaty and really need a shower right now.

340
00:29:43,780 --> 00:29:48,260
I’ll talk to you later then. Good night. Talk to you later. See ya!

341
00:30:46,860 --> 00:30:50,180
Finally, I get to work here where you used to, Dad.

342
00:30:52,300 --> 00:30:54,260
Please cheer for me.

343
00:31:11,730 --> 00:31:14,140
That one is Yellowstripe. I’ll show you.

344
00:31:14,200 --> 00:31:22,300
They’re sorting out fish since fishes often come in various sizes and types when we unload them from the boat.

345
00:31:22,300 --> 00:31:25,540
This one is Indian Mackerel. We put them in one category.

346
00:31:25,540 --> 00:31:27,860
This one is still fresh.

347
00:31:27,860 --> 00:31:32,730
Overall, that’s what we do here at the fisherman’s wharf. Let’s go see the office next, shall we?

348
00:31:32,930 --> 00:31:33,900
Okay.

349
00:31:34,300 --> 00:31:35,140
Let’s go.

350
00:31:35,780 --> 00:31:38,500
I’ll explain everything to you.

351
00:31:38,900 --> 00:31:45,620
It’s mainly here, the palm plantation, and the mine. Let’s go talk in the office.

352
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:05,300
My main businesses are fisherman’s wharf, oil palm plantation, and mining.

353
00:32:05,300 --> 00:32:08,540
For today, you can just take a look around first.

354
00:32:08,700 --> 00:32:14,340
Then, you can tell me later what you want to do and where you’d like to work.

355
00:32:14,340 --> 00:32:19,060
Or if you don’t like to stay outside because it’s hot, you can just work in the office.

356
00:32:20,100 --> 00:32:24,540
I’m so lucky indeed. My employer even lets me choose my own position.

357
00:32:24,560 --> 00:32:27,780
Well, it’s a privilege for my little one.

358
00:32:28,100 --> 00:32:31,940
I’ll give you a tour around the mine some day soon.

359
00:32:32,580 --> 00:32:38,060
Yes, Uncle. I’ll do my best at work to make it worth the tuition fees you paid for me.

360
00:32:38,800 --> 00:32:43,900
My dad said we are deeply indebted to you, so we should be grateful and repay the kindness.

361
00:32:48,360 --> 00:32:52,860
It’s actually your dad whom I’m indebted to.

362
00:32:53,560 --> 00:32:54,360
Yes?

363
00:32:57,060 --> 00:33:05,380
I promise I’ll take good care of you just like how I treat Fai.

364
00:33:08,100 --> 00:33:09,900
It’s all right, Uncle.

365
00:33:09,900 --> 00:33:15,100
I’m just a worker’s daughter. You’ve done a lot for me already.

366
00:33:15,100 --> 00:33:16,780
Okay!

367
00:33:18,760 --> 00:33:21,730
Go take a look around first.

368
00:33:21,900 --> 00:33:22,360
Yes.

369
00:33:22,360 --> 00:33:24,460
I’ll teach you what to do later.

370
00:33:35,660 --> 00:33:38,420
[Worker 1]: Look, that’s the Master’s new chick.

371
00:33:38,660 --> 00:33:39,460
[Worker 2]: Really?

372
00:33:39,460 --> 00:33:43,940
[Worker 1]: Yes! They were acting so lovey-dovey a minute ago.

373
00:33:43,940 --> 00:33:44,780
[Worker 2]: Really?

374
00:33:51,260 --> 00:33:55,380
Miss Phrao! Miss Phrao! Wait for me.

375
00:33:58,140 --> 00:33:59,800
Has the Master left?

376
00:34:01,360 --> 00:34:02,160
Mhm.

377
00:34:05,260 --> 00:34:08,100
Why are the workers looking at me like that? Is there something going on?

378
00:34:10,800 --> 00:34:14,500
Hmm, they’re probably excited to see the Master’s new chick.

379
00:34:14,580 --> 00:34:15,380
What?

380
00:34:19,659 --> 00:34:25,460
People at the wharf and plantation have been talking since yesterday that the Master just brought a new chick into the house.

381
00:34:25,460 --> 00:34:29,420
That’s why Young Master was so furious and kicked you out to stay at the worker’s cabin.

382
00:34:29,860 --> 00:34:30,400
What?

383
00:34:30,400 --> 00:34:34,699
And this morning, he even took you around being all cuddly and lovey-dovey in front of the workers.

384
00:34:35,600 --> 00:34:36,530
That’s not true!

385
00:34:37,500 --> 00:34:40,300
Aww, are you sure?

386
00:34:40,460 --> 00:34:42,760
Of course! Uncle and I are nothing like that.

387
00:34:44,400 --> 00:34:47,659
If Fai hears about this, wouldn’t she eat my head off?

388
00:34:49,699 --> 00:34:51,460
I guess it’s too late now.

389
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:52,730
What?

390
00:34:52,730 --> 00:34:53,940
She already knows.

391
00:34:54,860 --> 00:34:56,340
What did you just say, Auntie?

392
00:34:56,960 --> 00:35:01,160
Our workers are talking that Kaphrao is your dad’s mistress.

393
00:35:01,740 --> 00:35:09,340
That’s right, Miss. I saw it with my own eyes this morning that he was holding hands and being all touchy with Miss Kaphrao.

394
00:35:09,960 --> 00:35:13,060
Don’t tell me he’s planning to let her take over his business.

395
00:35:14,930 --> 00:35:16,660
Where’s that Gremlin right now?

396
00:36:05,860 --> 00:36:08,780
Damn! Too bad I missed it.

397
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:11,580
You jerk! Don’t you have eyes?

398
00:36:11,660 --> 00:36:13,580
Sorry, I just need to talk to you.

399
00:36:13,660 --> 00:36:16,900
Then why cut me off? Can’t you drive like normal people? What if I got killed?

400
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:18,980
Well, you’re still alive–can even bark at me too!

401
00:36:19,700 --> 00:36:20,980
What do you want?

402
00:36:23,160 --> 00:36:24,380
Why did you come back?

403
00:36:24,660 --> 00:36:27,260
I’m here to work–to repay Uncle’s kindness.

404
00:36:28,980 --> 00:36:32,700
Who would believe you? I know you’re itching to get your hands on my dad’s money.

405
00:36:32,700 --> 00:36:34,140
Why on earth would you ask then?

406
00:36:37,130 --> 00:36:39,740
But actually, that’s a good idea.

407
00:36:40,060 --> 00:36:43,700
I won’t have to work so hard that way. Why couldn’t I think of it earlier?

408
00:36:43,700 --> 00:36:44,940
Disgusting! Shame on you!

409
00:36:44,960 --> 00:36:45,860
You said it first.

410
00:36:46,900 --> 00:36:51,580
If I get to be the mistress here, that means I can boss you around, Buffalo Fai!

411
00:36:51,580 --> 00:36:56,340
I’m warning you, if you try to seduce my dad for his money–I’ll never let you live in peace!

412
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:59,700
Oh, I’m so scared.

413
00:36:59,700 --> 00:37:00,540
Guinea Pig!

414
00:37:00,660 --> 00:37:05,740
Shh! Call me Mummy so that you’ll get used to it.

415
00:37:06,660 --> 00:37:09,420
Come on, say it loud and clear.

416
00:37:15,460 --> 00:37:18,180
Sorry, forgot to tell you I’m a black belt.

417
00:37:24,600 --> 00:37:26,140
Does it hurt, my daughter?

418
00:37:29,700 --> 00:37:31,740
Mummy will fix it for you.

419
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:41,530
Dad! That bloody Guinea Pig just hurt me!

420
00:37:43,500 --> 00:37:44,860
Is what she said true?

421
00:37:45,400 --> 00:37:46,660
[Kaphrao]: Yes, Uncle.

422
00:37:50,600 --> 00:37:54,180
See? Just fire her. I don’t want to live under the same roof with her!

423
00:37:55,130 --> 00:37:56,000
Is that all?

424
00:37:57,460 --> 00:37:58,900
I still doubt it.

425
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:03,380
Why would the Little One hurt you with no rhyme or reason?

426
00:38:04,760 --> 00:38:07,100
I only did it to protect myself.

427
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:12,620
Are you saying I started it?

428
00:38:14,160 --> 00:38:17,380
She deliberately drove her car to cut in front of my bike.

429
00:38:17,380 --> 00:38:19,820
Luckily, nothing serious happened.

430
00:38:21,560 --> 00:38:22,580
Guinea Pig!

431
00:38:22,580 --> 00:38:25,540
You can check the footage on her dashcam, Uncle.

432
00:38:33,460 --> 00:38:37,700
Fai, do you have anything to say for yourself?

433
00:38:38,860 --> 00:38:44,220
You’re always unfair! If you’re going to take this Gremlin’s side, then don’t waste your time asking me.

434
00:38:44,220 --> 00:38:47,060
You never take your own daughter’s side anyway.

435
00:38:47,900 --> 00:38:48,930
Apologise to her.

436
00:38:50,460 --> 00:38:54,160
No way! If you feel so sorry for her, then say it yourself!

437
00:38:55,360 --> 00:38:57,980
Fai. Fai!

438
00:39:00,260 --> 00:39:02,740
Fai! Fai!

439
00:39:02,740 --> 00:39:04,060
Stop right now!

440
00:39:05,340 --> 00:39:08,500
Fai! Fai!

441
00:39:09,460 --> 00:39:11,940
Fai! Fai!

442
00:39:11,940 --> 00:39:15,020
Don’t you feel embarrassed acting all childish in front of her? Fai!

443
00:39:19,560 --> 00:39:21,500
I’m sorry she did that to you.

444
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:23,980
It’s my fault I didn’t raise her well.

445
00:39:23,980 --> 00:39:25,860
That’s why she’s being so troublesome.

446
00:39:26,600 --> 00:39:28,730
It’s my fault too, Uncle.

447
00:39:29,400 --> 00:39:32,180
Hey, don’t try to influence her.

448
00:39:32,460 --> 00:39:37,420
You’ve always been like this since little–keeping quiet no matter what she did to you.

449
00:39:37,420 --> 00:39:42,340
When I found out and wanted to punish her, you wouldn’t let me. I knew that.

450
00:39:42,860 --> 00:39:45,330
But now I think I can handle her.

451
00:39:45,660 --> 00:39:47,760
I’ll try to avoid clashing with her as much as I can.

452
00:39:48,760 --> 00:39:54,340
I know you’re a good girl, Little One. Please be patient with her.

453
00:39:54,340 --> 00:39:54,700
Yes.

454
00:39:54,730 --> 00:39:55,980
She’ll grow up soon.

455
00:39:57,130 --> 00:39:59,100
Actually, she’s all grown up now.

456
00:39:59,100 --> 00:40:02,260
But her personality is still unpleasant as ever.

457
00:40:05,060 --> 00:40:05,860
Exactly!

458
00:40:11,260 --> 00:40:13,660
Paen, get me something to eat! I’m hungry!

459
00:40:13,660 --> 00:40:15,060
Yes, Miss!

460
00:40:20,300 --> 00:40:21,260
Here you go.

461
00:40:29,730 --> 00:40:31,860
I don’t like basil leaves! Throw it away!

462
00:40:32,100 --> 00:40:34,220
Huh? Okay, Miss.

463
00:40:36,460 --> 00:40:38,620
Paen, bring it back!

464
00:40:40,020 --> 00:40:41,300
Not again.

465
00:41:02,260 --> 00:41:03,580
Holy shit!

466
00:41:06,500 --> 00:41:07,460
Is it okay?

467
00:41:11,660 --> 00:41:12,980
[Yod]: That’s good. Carry on.

468
00:41:12,980 --> 00:41:14,540
[Yod]: I’ll leave it to you then.

469
00:41:23,530 --> 00:41:25,340
[Yod]: Hi, Miss Phrao.

470
00:41:25,500 --> 00:41:26,980
Hello.

471
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:28,930
I heard you don’t seem to get along well with Young Master?

472
00:41:30,560 --> 00:41:32,780
I really don’t get it.

473
00:41:33,130 --> 00:41:35,780
What’s gotten into her head to have such a filthy thought?

474
00:41:35,980 --> 00:41:38,140
It’s understandable if she doesn’t trust me.

475
00:41:38,360 --> 00:41:40,700
But how could she not trust her own father?

476
00:41:41,330 --> 00:41:42,860
I really wonder how she grew up.

477
00:41:43,860 --> 00:41:45,540
Master is very popular.

478
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:48,780
Despite being a widower, many girls are lining up to be with him.

479
00:41:49,260 --> 00:41:51,060
He’s actually very loyal.

480
00:41:51,560 --> 00:41:55,660
After his wife passed away, he has never been with anyone except Miss Wanna.

481
00:41:56,700 --> 00:42:00,500
Miss Wanna? I’ve never met her.

482
00:42:00,600 --> 00:42:02,940
She lives in a small house at the back of the plantation.

483
00:42:03,130 --> 00:42:07,260
Master had tried to bring her into the main house but ended up having a big fight with Young Master.

484
00:42:07,260 --> 00:42:10,020
So, Miss Wanna had to live in another house instead.

485
00:42:10,020 --> 00:42:13,460
From then on, father and daughter have become estranged.

486
00:42:13,460 --> 00:42:15,700
Young Master hardly goes to the main house.

487
00:42:15,700 --> 00:42:17,660
She mostly sleeps at Miss Panee’s house.

488
00:42:19,260 --> 00:42:21,800
Wouldn’t Miss Wanna misunderstand me then?

489
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:25,500
Don’t worry. She’s generous and open-minded.

490
00:42:26,300 --> 00:42:27,580
Please excuse me.

491
00:42:44,760 --> 00:42:45,560
Thank you.

492
00:42:47,100 --> 00:42:49,930
Are you busy these days? You haven’t come here for a while.

493
00:42:52,260 --> 00:42:53,060
Yes.

494
00:42:54,660 --> 00:42:58,700
Kaphrao has just moved in so there are many things to take care of.

495
00:43:00,330 --> 00:43:04,940
I also heard about the rumour. It must have given you a headache.

496
00:43:06,360 --> 00:43:10,300
I suppose you don’t believe that rumour, do you?

497
00:43:13,330 --> 00:43:17,180
Of course not. I’ve been with you for so many years now.

498
00:43:18,300 --> 00:43:21,100
I know what kind of person you are.

499
00:43:21,800 --> 00:43:25,940
I don’t think I’ll ever find anyone as understanding as you.

500
00:43:26,860 --> 00:43:29,340
Despite what Fai did to you, you still–

501
00:43:29,340 --> 00:43:35,020
I’m happy to stay in my own place like this. Please don’t worry.

502
00:43:38,000 --> 00:43:38,800
Yes.

503
00:43:42,460 --> 00:43:47,860
But I still don’t understand why you want Kaphrao to live here?

504
00:43:51,760 --> 00:43:53,860
I love Kaphrao like my own daughter.

505
00:43:54,560 --> 00:43:56,460
I want my two kids to become close.

506
00:43:57,730 --> 00:44:02,540
Once Fai finally sees Kaphrao as her little sister, I’ll be able to die in peace.

507
00:44:09,600 --> 00:44:10,580
Want to have some?

508
00:44:10,980 --> 00:44:12,460
I’m all good.

509
00:44:35,130 --> 00:44:36,500
Hello, Miss Panee.

510
00:44:43,130 --> 00:44:46,530
Don’t you know it’s rude to keep someone older waiting this long?

511
00:44:48,360 --> 00:44:53,600
I really don’t know you’d be here, Miss Panee. Why don’t we go inside first?

512
00:44:54,000 --> 00:44:57,930
No need, I’m only here to say what I have to.

513
00:44:59,900 --> 00:45:02,700
I don’t know why you came back here.

514
00:45:03,420 --> 00:45:06,900
But I’m warning you, don’t ever cause my niece any trouble.

515
00:45:07,340 --> 00:45:11,460
Ak might be fond of you, but I’m not.

516
00:45:14,100 --> 00:45:15,930
I know my own place.

517
00:45:16,730 --> 00:45:19,060
I’ll try to stay away from her as best as I can.

518
00:45:21,460 --> 00:45:23,300
That’s good.

519
00:45:23,960 --> 00:45:25,900
I don’t want to waste my time talking to you.

520
00:45:28,260 --> 00:45:29,460
Goodbye, Miss–

521
00:45:52,400 --> 00:45:58,300
Dad, why does everyone here hate me?

522
00:46:05,260 --> 00:46:06,260
[Door knocking]

523
00:46:22,130 --> 00:46:25,160
Why? Are you surprised to see me?

524
00:46:27,100 --> 00:46:29,060
Buffa–Fai!

525
00:46:29,300 --> 00:46:32,740
Yes, it’s me. Who else do you think?

526
00:46:33,100 --> 00:46:37,700
Or are you expecting my dad or one of the workers?

527
00:46:37,700 --> 00:46:40,220
Disgusting! I just didn’t expect you’d come.

528
00:46:40,220 --> 00:46:42,340
Why didn’t you call first?

529
00:46:43,160 --> 00:46:44,660
This house is also my property.

530
00:46:45,130 --> 00:46:49,100
I don’t need anyone’s approval to come here. Move!

531
00:46:49,460 --> 00:46:52,500
Hey! Get out! What are you doing?

532
00:46:52,800 --> 00:46:57,530
Checking if you’re planning something evil, or arranging your bed for my father.

533
00:46:57,760 --> 00:46:58,560
Nonsense!

534
00:47:00,760 --> 00:47:02,020
That’s my room!

535
00:47:04,060 --> 00:47:07,900
From now on, you must come to Aunt Panee’s house to eat with me every single day.

536
00:47:08,180 --> 00:47:10,660
So that you won’t have time to seduce my dad.

537
00:47:10,760 --> 00:47:14,220
No! Eating with you? Just a thought of that makes me want to puke.

538
00:47:14,220 --> 00:47:15,340
I’ll just puke on your face!

539
00:47:15,530 --> 00:47:16,900
But that’s an order!

540
00:47:18,260 --> 00:47:23,980
Listen, first, you’re not my boss. You don’t have the right to tell me what to do.

541
00:47:23,980 --> 00:47:26,980
And even if you’re my boss–which is absolutely impossible–

542
00:47:26,980 --> 00:47:31,900
you can only tell me what to do at work. If it’s not work, then dream on!

543
00:47:32,800 --> 00:47:36,180
Fine! You said it yourself.

544
00:47:43,160 --> 00:47:46,660
Morning, Miss Phrao! Come eat something first, come on.

545
00:47:48,930 --> 00:47:50,340
Where are you off too?

546
00:47:50,460 --> 00:47:53,220
Master said Uncle Yod will come take me to the mine.

547
00:47:53,360 --> 00:47:58,020
Oh, really? Don’t forget to apply lots of sunscreen then.

548
00:47:58,100 --> 00:48:01,180
It’s boiling hot as if you were in hell there.

549
00:48:01,700 --> 00:48:02,760
Is it that hot?

550
00:48:03,300 --> 00:48:09,740
Yes, I used to ask Young Master to let me work there because I wanted to be surrounded by strong and muscular men.

551
00:48:09,740 --> 00:48:14,180
But once I got there, I’d rather stay home on the island.

552
00:48:15,860 --> 00:48:17,260
Have it. Eat all you like.

553
00:48:17,260 --> 00:48:20,980
[Phone ringing]

554
00:48:22,860 --> 00:48:27,740
Yes, Uncle Yod? Okay, I’ll be waiting outside.

555
00:48:29,500 --> 00:48:30,300
Yes.

556
00:48:31,730 --> 00:48:33,620
Uncle Yod is coming. I’m heading out then.

557
00:48:33,730 --> 00:48:35,130
- Okay.
- I’ll have this then.

558
00:48:35,160 --> 00:48:36,700
Sure, take some more.

559
00:48:36,860 --> 00:48:37,980
Thanks, this is fine.

560
00:48:37,980 --> 00:48:39,060
- Hey, Miss Phrao!
- Yeah?

561
00:48:39,060 --> 00:48:41,500
Don’t forget to put on sunscreen. It’s extremely hot there, trust me.

562
00:48:41,660 --> 00:48:42,460
Okay!

563
00:48:49,800 --> 00:48:50,940
Why are you here?

564
00:48:51,760 --> 00:48:53,300
To take you to work, of course.

565
00:48:54,130 --> 00:48:54,930
What?

566
00:48:55,200 --> 00:48:57,780
My dad already agreed to let you work with me.

567
00:48:58,340 --> 00:49:01,420
From now on, you’re my assistant.

568
00:49:24,300 --> 00:49:25,780
Trying to please me?

569
00:49:26,960 --> 00:49:30,740
I’m going to officially help you at work. No more dragging my feet.

570
00:49:31,760 --> 00:49:32,780
Are you serious?

571
00:49:33,400 --> 00:49:41,800
I’ll do anything you assign me to do and attend every meeting, but only on one condition.

572
00:49:43,200 --> 00:49:44,000
What condition?

573
00:49:47,160 --> 00:49:49,700
You have to let Kaphrao be my assistant.

574
00:49:54,960 --> 00:50:00,900
Come on, I know what you’re thinking. Aren’t you going to give me a chance?

575
00:50:02,960 --> 00:50:07,020
Fine, I’ll trust you this time.

576
00:50:08,620 --> 00:50:09,700
Deal?

577
00:50:11,730 --> 00:50:12,380
Deal.

578
00:50:17,200 --> 00:50:18,900
Am I your friend or what?

579
00:50:20,100 --> 00:50:22,500
Here, have some more.

580
00:50:31,780 --> 00:50:37,300
From now on, you have to do whatever I say because I’m now officially your boss.

581
00:50:39,460 --> 00:50:41,220
You’re plotting something evil, aren’t you?

582
00:50:41,220 --> 00:50:46,100
No! Why would you think that? All I have is sincerity.

583
00:50:46,420 --> 00:50:47,380
Get in the car.

584
00:50:51,740 --> 00:50:52,980
Young Master!

585
00:50:55,460 --> 00:50:56,580
Young Master.

586
00:50:56,580 --> 00:50:59,100
Are you going to take Miss Phrao to the mine yourself?

587
00:51:00,130 --> 00:51:01,540
Yes, is there a problem?

588
00:51:01,860 --> 00:51:07,860
No, Miss. Actually, she can come with me since I have to go to work there anyway.

589
00:51:07,860 --> 00:51:10,860
I also plan to show her around the mine to learn some work.

590
00:51:12,560 --> 00:51:14,540
That’s all right, just leave it to me.

591
00:51:14,540 --> 00:51:17,780
You can go take care of something else. Don’t worry about her.

592
00:51:22,060 --> 00:51:23,740
Okay, Miss.

593
00:51:37,200 --> 00:51:39,500
Stop standing like an idiot there. Get in the car!

594
00:52:42,130 --> 00:52:45,020
Why do you want me as your assistant if you don’t like me?

595
00:52:45,020 --> 00:52:47,860
And you even volunteer to take me around the mine.

596
00:52:48,800 --> 00:52:51,220
You’re not planning to kill me and dump my body there, are you?

597
00:52:52,530 --> 00:52:57,780
Good idea. Thanks for your suggestion. Why couldn’t I think of it earlier?

598
00:52:59,100 --> 00:53:00,820
Don’t you dare mock me.

599
00:53:02,730 --> 00:53:06,660
I just want to show you around the mine and give you a 101 mining lesson.

600
00:53:07,160 --> 00:53:08,160
But I don’t want to know it.

601
00:53:08,500 --> 00:53:11,000
Only speak when I ask you to. Don’t try to cozy up to me.

602
00:53:14,660 --> 00:53:16,500
What faculty did you graduate from?

603
00:53:21,100 --> 00:53:22,600
Hey, I’m asking you!

604
00:53:23,260 --> 00:53:25,730
Oh, you’re talking to me?

605
00:53:26,900 --> 00:53:30,100
It’s just us here. If not you, then who the heck I’d be talking to?

606
00:53:30,100 --> 00:53:31,580
I thought you were talking to your imaginary friend.

607
00:53:31,580 --> 00:53:32,460
Answer me!

608
00:53:35,200 --> 00:53:36,200
Accounting.

609
00:53:38,000 --> 00:53:41,860
Unbelievable, you don’t look like someone who’s educated.

610
00:53:43,800 --> 00:53:46,940
And you don’t look like someone who has brains.

611
00:54:14,760 --> 00:54:20,220
You agreed to let Kaphrao work with Fai, does that mean you trust her?

612
00:54:21,460 --> 00:54:22,620
Not at all.

613
00:54:23,760 --> 00:54:28,340
I think Fai is definitely planning to fire Kaphrao.

614
00:54:29,600 --> 00:54:32,500
But I trust Kaphrao that she can handle Fai.

615
00:54:36,130 --> 00:54:38,660
I’m afraid those two might end up strangling each other first.

616
00:54:40,160 --> 00:54:41,730
Well, let them be.

617
00:54:42,330 --> 00:54:45,540
Fighting each other might make them become closer.

618
00:54:45,800 --> 00:54:52,420
Just wait and see. I’ll make those two love each other like real siblings.

619
00:54:59,300 --> 00:55:00,580
Need a little booster.

620
00:55:04,800 --> 00:55:06,140
What’s so funny?

621
00:55:06,900 --> 00:55:08,500
You, of course.

622
00:55:09,330 --> 00:55:10,580
Can I have more?

623
00:55:12,380 --> 00:55:15,500
[Akanee Crushing Plant]

624
00:55:15,500 --> 00:55:17,340
Can you have it inspected?

625
00:55:17,340 --> 00:55:21,260
I think there’s a problem with the brake. It feels squishy and doesn’t stop well.

626
00:55:21,260 --> 00:55:22,260
Yes, Miss.

627
00:55:22,260 --> 00:55:24,620
Take care of it for me then. I’ll wait in the office.

628
00:55:38,200 --> 00:55:40,460
We blew up that mountain earlier.

629
00:55:40,600 --> 00:55:42,660
Then, we’ll put those stones into the crushing plant.

630
00:55:42,760 --> 00:55:45,930
After that, we’ll sort them out into different sizes just like what you see there.

631
00:55:48,900 --> 00:55:51,220
Wow! It’s huge.

632
00:55:52,300 --> 00:55:54,730
Where you’re standing now is called the office building.

633
00:55:55,500 --> 00:56:02,340
It’s for keeping records and documents like a list of clients who buy rocks from us, or vehicles coming in and out of the mine.

634
00:56:04,460 --> 00:56:07,860
I can’t believe you’re really teaching me some work.

635
00:56:09,500 --> 00:56:11,140
I told you.

636
00:56:13,360 --> 00:56:15,260
I need to go through some documents first.

637
00:56:15,260 --> 00:56:17,900
You can go look around or explore the place however you like.

638
00:56:30,900 --> 00:56:31,980
Damn it!

639
00:56:33,930 --> 00:56:34,730
What?

640
00:56:36,700 --> 00:56:39,780
The dump truck tickets are with Uncle Yod. What to do?

641
00:56:48,260 --> 00:56:49,540
Why are you looking at me?

642
00:56:51,260 --> 00:56:52,820
Can you go get it for me?

643
00:56:52,820 --> 00:56:54,700
I have some work to finish off here.

644
00:56:55,500 --> 00:56:56,300
Get it from where?

645
00:56:57,500 --> 00:57:01,100
Behind that mountain over there.

646
00:57:04,260 --> 00:57:08,980
What? Hang on, how do you expect me to go there?

647
00:57:09,660 --> 00:57:15,380
They already took my car for a brake inspection. I guess you’ll have to walk there.

648
00:57:15,460 --> 00:57:16,580
Walk?

649
00:57:37,530 --> 00:57:41,700
[Next Episode]
Young Master said if you can’t finish it today, then you’re not allowed to go home.

650
00:57:42,060 --> 00:57:44,100
Fine! This is a piece of cake!

651
00:57:44,530 --> 00:57:46,420
[Fai]: Is that girl still working?

652
00:57:46,530 --> 00:57:50,180
[Yod]: Yes, are you sure you want to leave her there alone, Young Master?

653
00:57:50,360 --> 00:57:52,740
[Yod]: It’s quite dark and deserted around there at night.

654
00:57:53,900 --> 00:57:55,160
Well, she chose it herself.

655
00:57:55,360 --> 00:57:57,300
It’s not like I’ve forced her to stay back so late.

656
00:58:03,930 --> 00:58:08,220
I’m really curious what makes you change this much?

657
00:58:09,700 --> 00:58:10,860
It’s you.

658
00:58:31,260 --> 00:58:38,300
♫I still remember vividly that day when we first met♫

659
00:58:38,860 --> 00:58:44,620
♫Those memories we had together never fade away from my heart♫

660
00:58:44,980 --> 00:58:52,580
♫We might never say it out loud how we feel for each other♫

661
00:58:52,580 --> 00:58:58,340
♫But deep down we both know how we feel♫

662
00:58:58,340 --> 00:59:04,500
♫Those things in the past, I still can’t forget them♫

663
00:59:04,500 --> 00:59:10,580
♫I want to know if you’re like that too–do you also feel the same?♫

664
00:59:10,980 --> 00:59:18,540
♫I could never forget those eyes of yours♫

665
00:59:18,540 --> 00:59:24,980
♫The warmth you used to give me, I still remember it vividly♫

666
00:59:25,300 --> 00:59:32,340
♫No matter for how long, you’ll always remain in my heart♫

667
00:59:32,340 --> 00:59:42,740
♫All those years I’ve been waiting, for us to finally be together again♫

668
00:59:50,780 --> 00:59:54,700
[North Star Entertainment]

669
00:59:54,700 --> 00:59:58,700
[Flaming Chains of Love]

